#
# This file describes the prompt for the $PROMPT_NAME prompt.
#
# It is a collection of settings that make up the actual prompt.
#
# The prompt settings are delimited by a line containing only a
# single '.'.  The settings are:
#
#   1.  The prompt name.  This is a short string that identifies
#       the prompt.  It is used to name the prompt file.
#
#   2.  The prompt type.  This is a string that identifies the
#       prompt type.  It is used to determine which prompt
#       generator to use to generate the actual prompt.
#
#   3.  The prompt description.  This is a short string that
#       describes the prompt.  It is used to generate the
#       prompt description file.
#
#   4.  The prompt directory.  This is
